Build ubuntu-plucky sdcard for orangepi 5 plus:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-plucky/linaro-rootfs.img
                                    /linaro-esp.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD and wifi usb dongle to SBC.
Esc -> Boot Manager -> ( sdcard, emmc userdata or the last UEFI )
Run setup
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
free
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc vlc vlc-plugin-video-output

sudo apt install snapd
sudo systemctl restart snapd
sudo snap refresh
sudo snap install mpv

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 2 rockchip-hdmi0 as default )

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install firefox-esr
firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan-temp.mp4 --merge-output-format mp4 && ffmpeg -hide_banner -loglevel error -i swan-temp.mp4 -c:v libx265 -pix_fmt yuv420p -crf 28 -preset faster -c:a copy swan.mp4  ( It may take 25 minutes )
mpv --hwdec=auto-copy swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

Plugin ASUS USB-BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to opi5+.
sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
